body:
I was concerned the code change is against the initial design and we may be doing it without understanding all the implications. But, since we dont have any better solution and the current set of tests we have are positive with the change, I would :+1:  this. Though, we should keep in mind that this may lead to some regressions like CLOUDSTACK-3681 or CLOUDSTACK-6478

@mike-tutkowski Can you also test if the vmware snapshot-from-template issue you faced is fixed by this?

@ustcweizhou Thanks for fixing it very quickly. A little description would have saved me sometime in trying to find the root cause :)

ok, so
if (destpool == null) {
    throw new CloudRuntimeException("missing storage pool");
}
or something like that? Or would you rather see a NullPointerException?

@ustcweizhou Can you please share FS or design document for this work?
It'd help greatly in reviewing this patch.
Thanks.

+1 move this test out of BVTs - this was brought up on almost 3-4 weeks ago. 
@runseb - I guess, my understanding is - we need 100% passrate on all BVTs - we cannot have any skipped or failed.  In this case not everyone will have a nicira appliance and be able to test it.  Hence it fails to be a common BVT - it can be a BVT for someone who has a nicira appliance.  That said, If someone has any specific test(s) that only they can run - keep them in a separate folder.   This was discussed in an email chain almost 4 weeks ago and we left it open. well enough said on this, :-) 

